sentences: Jemeel Moondoc (August 5, 1946 – August 29, 2021) was a jazz saxophonist who played alto saxophone.
In 1984, he formed the Jus Grew Orchestra, which secured a residency at the Neither/Nor club in the Lower East Side.
He worked with Parker again in 1998's album, New World Pygmies.
He died in August 2021, at the age of 75 from the effects of sickle cell anemia.
